<br>
Run 3 (done)<br>
Regen 3 (almost done -- went on vacation for Christmas)<br>
<br>
Mastery 3<br>
<br>
Pet discipline<br>
Frenzied Burnout<br>
<br>
Except for soloing and possibly level 1 clarity, mastery seems to provide almost the most regen and largest increase in mana pool. <br>
<br>
Making a spec check seems to confer about a 30% increase in efficiency (totally unscientific gut feeling perception from playing this long). Therefore a 5 % chance of a spec check is worth about 1.5% increase in efficiency. Add in reduced fizzles and  I'd &quot;value&quot; level 1 mastery about as much as a 2% increase in efficiency AND mana pool.<br>
<br>
My mana regen typically hovers around 30-33 pts/tick (less if soloing) except under certain circumstances when mana regen is super high. So except while soloing one point of clarity is worth at most about a 3.3% efficiency and a tiny increase (&lt;1%) in mana pool. So the first level of mental clarity may be worth it (assuming efficiency matters more than mana pool) and higher levels are not worth it (since they cost more). <p>Cydmab Promethean, Triune <BR>
Level 60 Arch-Mage, Morell Thule <BR>
Die by lava, die by flame, Erudite mages kill and maim!
